translated: Holmgren, Sven Gösta, licensed physician, from Vänersborg, born October 28, 1909, in Stockholm, to the merchant prince Ludvig and Anna Jakobsson. He married medical student Gunnel Krok in 1944 and they have a son named Nils, born in 1945. Holmgren passed his final exam at the Norra Real school in Stockholm in 1929. He received his medical degree in 1932 and medical licence in Stockholm in 1937. He worked as an assistant physician at the radiology department at St. Erik's Hospital in Stockholm in 1937, as well as an intern physician at the radiology department at the hospital in Borås from 1938 to 1939, at the hospital in Simrishamn from 1940 to 1941, and at the medical department at the hospital in Borås from 1941 to 1942. From 1943, he was the senior intern physician at the medical department at the hospital in Vänersborg, and from 1947, he served as a medical officer at the Swedish Air Force in Tirol. His hobbies include hunting.
